    "body": "The loading spinner would get stuck indefinitely if the backend\nAPI (/api/auth/me) did not respond within a reasonable time, since\nfetch() has no built-in timeout and setLoading(false) was only\ncalled after the awaited fetchProfile resolved.\n\nTwo fixes applied to auth-provider.tsx:\n- Add AbortController with 10s timeout to the fetch call inside\n  fetchProfile so a slow/unresponsive backend no longer blocks auth\n- Add a 15s safety timeout on the overall loading state in case\n  Firebase onAuthStateChanged never fires (e.g. Firebase init fails)\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Liov6x2cGpmGmB1kqDaAoY\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **Bug Fixes**\n  * Improved authentication reliability with timeout protections to prevent indefinite loading states during sign-in.\n  * Enhanced error handling and reporting for authentication API failures and token retrieval issues.\n  * Optimized resource cleanup to ensure proper management during authentication state transitions.\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
